PCRE2 and Tomcat Connectors
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Using PCRE2
-----------

The Windows ISAPI Redirector, which is part of the Tomcat Connectors
project, can use PCRE2 based regular expressions to rewrite URLs.

The rewrite rules must be put into a file, whose path and name
are given via the key rewrite_rule_file either in the registry
or the isapi_redirect.properties file.

Rewriting is done after mapping requests via uriworkermap.properties.

There are two types of rewrite rules:

- simple prefix rules (not using PCRE2):

/original/path/prefix=/some/new/path/prefix

- regular expression rules:

~PATTERN=REPLACEMENT

Example for a regular expression rule:

~/([^/]+)/([^/]+)/=/myapp/$2/$1


Adding and maintaining PCRE2 in the sources
-------------------------------------------

The sub directory "pcre2" contains the extracted contents of the
original PCRE2 source download in zip form.

Two files have been added:

- pcre2/config.h.win
  This is a simple file defining what type of PCRE2 build
  is requested. It should be pretty stable over time.

- pcre2/Makefile.vc
  This is a simple Makefile, which should also be pretty
  stable. If PCRE2 needs new file to be build after an update,
  they have to be added to the OBJECTS list.

The type of PCRE2 library we build, has the following properties:

- static library
- code unit width 8 (for ASCII and UTF-8)
- no posix library build
- no pcre2grep or test build

